parameters.name: EndUserId
parameters.description: The value of the attributes.service.app.user_id field in the trace record. It can contain upper and lower case letters, digits, dot (.), hyphen (-), and underscore (\_). It is empty by default.

parameters.name: HasEvents
parameters.description: Whether to return only trace records containing spans with a non-empty events. Example: Suppose a trace has 3 spans. If this parameter is True, this trace meets the condition when any one of the 3 spans has a non-empty events. The default value is False. The events is not used for filtering.

parameters.name: HasStatusMessage
parameters.description: Whether to return only trace records containing spans with a non-empty statusMessage. Example: Suppose a trace has 3 spans. If this parameter is True, this trace meets the condition when any one of the 3 spans has a non-empty statusMessage. The default value is False. The statusMessage is not used for filtering.

parameters.name: LlmAppName
parameters.description: The value of the resources.service.app.name field in the trace record. It can contain upper and lower case letters, digits, dot (.), hyphen (-), and underscore (\_). Must be an exact match. It is empty by default.

parameters.name: MaxTime
parameters.description: The upper limit of the search time range, in UTC format (YYYY-mm-dd or YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm:ss). By default, the value is (current time +10 minutes)

parameters.name: MinTime
parameters.description: The lower limit of the search time range, in UTC format (YYYY-mm-dd or YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm:ss). By default, the value is (current time - 2 days).

parameters.name: OpentelemetryCompatible
parameters.description: Whether the returned JSON data can be directly converted to OpenTelemetry TracesData protobuf object. Default value: False. JSON data that is compatible with OpenTelemetry is more complex. Such data is generally not required unless you want to generate a protobuf object of OpenTelemetry.

parameters.name: OwnerSubId
parameters.description: The value of the resources.service.owner.sub_id field in the trace record. It can contain upper and lower case letters, digits, dot (.), hyphen (-), and underscore (\_). It is empty by default.

parameters.name: PageNumber
parameters.description: The page number. Page starts from page 1. Default value: 1

parameters.name: PageSize
parameters.description: The number of entries per page. Default value: 20. Maximum value: 100.

parameters.name: SortBy
parameters.description: The field used to sort the returned results. Valid values: StartTime and Duration.

parameters.name: SpanIds
parameters.description: The list of span IDs. Each trace record contains one or more spans.

parameters.name: TraceReduceMethod
parameters.description:
The content simplification method for returned trace data to reduce the data volume.

REMOVE_EMBEDDING: Removes all embedding array contents.

ROOT_ONLY: Returns only the root span for each trace, with the root span content also having the REMOVE_EMBEDDING applied.

Blank: Maintains the original data without simplification.
